Very soon, on 8 October, the criminal proceedings against János Zuchlag and his accomplices will begin.
The politician and his accomplices are accused of committing fraud of significant harm, in a business way, continuously and in an organized manner in addition to other crimes, including falsification of documents.
According to the Office of the Prosecutor, the funds obtained in public tenders were used for their own purposes, often justifying the performance of the tasks with false invoices.
The public funds and that of the municipalities - as a whole some 65 million HUF - stopped in part in the treasury of the Fiatal Baloldal organization and in part in the pocket of individuals.
The method, which was also made known by researchers, was to justify the collection of funds obtained in public tenders with false invoices behind which there was no actual execution, the different associations never fulfilled their obligations.
